(1) Implementation of epidural analgesia for labor to all patients;

This standard is mentioned as one of the four standards measured during the audit cycle. The text states that "During the audit period epidural analgesia increased from 15.5% of all labors in the first trimester of the study to 51% in the last trimester (p<0.005)". This suggests that the standard of implementing epidural analgesia for labor was reached, but not necessarily in all women, as the percentage of patients receiving epidural analgesia increased over time, but did not reach 100%.
